{"id": "duc04-testb-15:9#29", "contents": "The impact of Shepard's death was felt far beyond Casper, with vigils and rallies held across the country to condemn the brutal attack and advocate for greater protections for the LGBTQ+ community. In Washington, D.C., a large rally was held on the steps of the Capitol, with members of Congress and activists calling for passage of a federal bill that would add extra penalties to crimes motivated by a victim's sexual orientation, gender or disability. The House of Representatives passed a resolution condemning Shepard's killing and urging action to prevent similar tragedies in the future. As the nation mourned Shepard's loss, it also came together to demand greater justice and equality for all."}
